metadata.name: TOIVO #1
metadata.description:
Vuosaari – Helsinki, Finland, 2019

Sometimes it can be hard to envisioning what the final image will look like, I might have an idea of how I’m going to shoot it and process it, but in this case I had no idea how it was going to turn out. I worked with the image to bring focus where I felt it needed it and taking away from areas that I didn’t feel it needed it. It took me over a long time to process it, with each step I made I found something new or something that needed to be improved. I’m really pleased how it came out. This is one of my favourite photographs that I have taken for over a decade.  


**Properties** 

**Resolution:** 7500X5000

**Shutter speed:** 4 minute 37 s 

**Lens Aperture:**  f/5.6  

**Focal length:** 23mm 

**ISO:** 100 

**Time of day:** Twilights

**Genre:** Fine art Black & White

**Technique:** Long exposure
